es.fnl.fsm
Class ExactMatcher<E>

java.lang.Object
  es.fnl.fsm.ExactMatcher<E>

public final class ExactMatcher<E>
extends Object

This matcher implements sequence comparison between Lists using the Boyer-Moore pattern matching algorithm.

As this is an exact matcher, elements are compared using equals(Object). Note that the empty pattern is illegal, while a null in the pattern is allowed to match a null in the sequence if at the right position.

Author:
Florian Leitner

find

public int find(List<E> sequence,
                int offset)
Find the index at which the pattern matches in the sequence at or after the offset.

Find uses the Booyer-Moore algorithm; Therefore, the approach will use index access ( get(int) ) on the List, so it is recommended not to use linked lists as input.

Parameters:
sequence - list to align the pattern with
offset - index in sequence where to start the alignments
Returns:
the offset of the match or -1 if no match is found
